  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Patient Admission Executive (West)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Register patients at the Emergency Medicine Department</li><li>Collect payments for A&E fees and inpatient deposits</li><li>Provide basic financial counselling to patients and relatives</li><li>Handle counter and phone enquiries using proper telephone etiquette</li><li>Assist patients and visitors with enquiries and special needs</li><li>Provide updates to patients’ relatives by liaising with doctors and nurses</li><li>Support patient discharge and appointment booking </li><li>Ensure counters, waiting areas, equipment, and materials are well maintained</li><li>Sort and manage patient records and e-cards</li><li>Follow up on enquiries and appointment requests within required timelines</li><li>Resolve service issues and patient relations matters</li><li>Comply with hospital policies and procedures</li><li>Participate in daily briefings, meetings, and service improvement activities</li><li>Perform other duties as assigned by supervisors</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>At least GCE ‘N’/‘O’ level education </li><li>Possess Class 3 or 4 License </li><li>Practical Knowledge of hospital operations is an added advantage </li><li>Proficiency in computer skills (MS Office) </li><li>Demonstrate good interpersonal and communication skills </li><li>Display compassion, a positive and caring attitude towards patients, internal and external clients </li><li>Willing to work 3 rotating shifts </li></ul><p><strong>** This Singapore-based position is opened to Singaporeans only.</strong></p><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified. </p><p>GMP Technologies (S) Pte Ltd   |   EA Licence:11C3793   |   Nurul Amirah |   Registration No: R22108940</p>",
